# Visitor Counter & Timestamp Feature

Add a visitor counter and visitor log (with timestamps) to the portfolio site. Only visible to you (Hardik) via a secret admin panel.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Firebase Project Required**: This feature needs Firebase Realtime Database to store visitor data across all visitors. You'll need to:
> 1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/)
> 2. Create a new project (or reuse your existing one)
> 3. Enable **Realtime Database** (not Firestore) → set rules to allow read/write
> 4. Copy the Firebase config (apiKey, databaseURL, etc.)
>
> **Do you already have a Firebase project set up? If so, please share the config.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Admin Access**: The admin panel will be hidden from normal visitors. You'll access it by adding `?admin=hardik` to your URL (e.g., `yoursite.com?admin=hardik`). Would you prefer a different secret key or a keyboard shortcut instead?

## How It Works

1. **Every visitor** that opens your site → counter increments by 1 and their visit is logged (timestamp, date, browser info)
2. **Only you** can see the stats by adding `?admin=hardik` to the URL
3. An **admin dashboard panel** slides in from the bottom-right showing:
   - Total visitor count
   - List of recent visits with date, time, and browser info
   - A close button to hide it

